gomodel:SYNGO_3965  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: ATG-9 mutants exhibit a defect in autophagosome biogenesis in axons during development (Fig. 5) that is required to regulate presynapse (Fig.1-3) and active zone (Fig. 4) assembly.. Experimental description: All worms were cultivated at 20°C on NGM plates seeded with OP50 E. coli. As a wild type reference strain, we utilized N2 Bristol worms." ;
